definition:
A woman descended from Ephrathah of the tribe of Judah  living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at 1Ch.2.19; married to Caleb (H3612H); 
 mother of: Hur (H2354); also called Ephrath at 1Ch.2.19; 
Group of eph.ra.tah (אֶפְרָ֫תָה "Ephrathah" H0672)
 § Ephrathite = "ashiness: fruitfulness"
1) an inhabitant or descendant of Ephraim (in in Jdg.12.5; 1Ki.11.26) 
2) an inhabitant of Bethlehem (in Rut.1.1; 1Sa.1.1; 1Sa.17.12)
